      <p>
        As the table illustrates, the tax burden on the tredicesima increases significantly at higher income levels. A worker earning a RAL of 20,000 euros takes home approximately 70% of the gross tredicesima, while a worker earning 50,000 euros keeps only about 52%. This disparity is due to the progressive nature of the Italian IRPEF system: those whose income falls into the 43% marginal bracket face nearly double the tax rate compared to those in the 23% bracket.
      </p>
      <p>
        For a precise calculation based on your specific RAL, number of months worked, and personal tax situation, use the calculator above. The simulator automatically applies the correct IRPEF marginal rate and INPS contribution to provide an accurate estimate of your net tredicesima for December 2026.
      </p>

